5 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Approval of grants -- completion of biennial appropriation. (1) The
6 legislature, pursuant to 22-3-1305, authorizes grants for the projects specified in [section 1(2)].
7 (2) The authorization of these grants completes a biennial appropriation from the historic
8 preservation grant program account established in 22-3-1307.
9 (3) Grants to entities from prior biennia are reauthorized for the completion of contract work.
10
11 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Condition of grants -- disbursement of funds. (1) The disbursement of
12 grant funds for the projects specified in [section 1(2)] is subject to the completion of the following conditions:
13 (a) The grant recipient shall document that other matching funds required for the completion of the
14 project are firmly committed.
15 (b) The grant recipient must have a project management plan that is approved by the department
16 of commerce.
17 (c) The grant recipient must be in compliance with the auditing and reporting requirements
18 provided for in 2-7-503 and establish a financial accounting system that the department can reasonably ensure
19 conforms to generally accepted accounting principles. Tribal governments shall comply with the auditing and
20 reporting requirements provided for in 2 CFR 200.
21 (d) The grant recipient shall satisfactorily comply with any conditions described in the application or
22 project summaries section of the Montana historic preservation grant program 2025 biennium report to the 69th
23 legislature.
24 (e) The grant recipient shall satisfy other specific requirements considered necessary by the
25 department of commerce to accomplish the purpose of the project as evidenced by the application to the
26 department.
27 (f) The grant recipient shall execute a grant agreement with the department of commerce.
